---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Navbar from "../components/Navbar.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout title="About - 12 in 12">
  <div class="min-h-screen flex flex-col">
    <Navbar />

    <main class="flex-1 bg-slate-900 pt-32 pb-16">
      <div class="relative">
        <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-grid-slate-800/[0.1] bg-[size:40px_40px]"></div>
        <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-b from-slate-900/50 to-slate-900"></div>

        <article class="relative mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 prose prose-invert prose-slate">

          {/* Current Vision */}
          <div class="text-center mb-16">
            <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white sm:text-4xl">
              About 12 in 12
            </h1>
            <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-slate-400">
              A community for builders who bet on themselves
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="space-y-12">
            <section>
              <h2 class="text-gradient">What is 12 in 12?</h2>
              <p>
                12 in 12 is a community platform for builders who commit to shipping
                things they care about. "Betting on yourself" means putting your time
                and skills on the line for something you believe in — whether that's
                a business, a cause, or your own growth.
              </p>
              <p>
                The name started as a challenge: build 12 products in 12 months. The
                spirit remains — bet, build, ship, reflect — but the platform now
                serves builders at any pace.
              </p>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2 class="text-gradient">Three Reasons to Build</h2>
              <div class="grid gap-4 not-prose">
                <div class="bg-emerald-900/20 rounded-xl p-5 border border-emerald-700/30">
                  <h3 class="text-emerald-400 font-semibold mb-1">For Profit</h3>
                  <p class="text-slate-300 text-sm">Build a business. Find customers. Test if your idea has legs.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-blue-900/20 rounded-xl p-5 border border-blue-700/30">
                  <h3 class="text-blue-400 font-semibold mb-1">For Impact</h3>
                  <p class="text-slate-300 text-sm">Solve a real problem for your community. Ship tools that help people.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-purple-900/20 rounded-xl p-5 border border-purple-700/30">
                  <h3 class="text-purple-400 font-semibold mb-1">For Craft</h3>
                  <p class="text-slate-300 text-sm">Learn by doing. Experiment with new tech. Build something you're proud of.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2 class="text-gradient">How It Works</h2>
              <p>
                Every builder gets a profile page that tells their story. When you
                place a bet, you set your thesis — what you're building and why. As
                you build, the platform prompts you to share progress, milestones,
                and learnings. When you ship (or park, or pivot), you reflect on what
                happened.
              </p>
              <p>
                The community feed shows what everyone is building in real time. You
                learn from others' journeys, leave comments, and find builders who
                inspire you.
              </p>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2 class="text-gradient">Who Built This?</h2>
              <p>
                <a href="/dorelljames" class="text-primary-400 hover:text-primary-300">Dorell James</a>
                — a developer from the Philippines who wanted a community to share
                the journey of building products. After launching
                <a href="https://hapsay.com" class="text-primary-400 hover:text-primary-300" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">hapsay.com</a>,
                he realized building is lonely. Having people to share it with, learn from,
                and build alongside makes all the difference.
              </p>
              <p>
                12 in 12 itself is one of his bets. It originally launched with the strict
                "12 products in 12 months" pitch. Real builders showed up. But over time,
                the format needed to evolve. This is the relaunch — same spirit, broader vision.
              </p>
            </section>

            <hr class="border-slate-700" />

            {/* Origin Story — collapsible */}
            <section>
              <details class="group">
                <summary class="cursor-pointer text-primary-400 hover:text-primary-300 font-semibold text-lg flex items-center gap-2 list-none">
                  <svg class="w-5 h-5 transition-transform group-open:rotate-90" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7" />
                  </svg>
                  Read the original origin story (2025)
                </summary>

                <div class="mt-6 space-y-8 border-l-2 border-slate-700 pl-6">
                  <blockquote class="border-l-4 border-primary-500 pl-4 italic text-lg text-slate-400">
                    "Everything around you that you call life was made up by people that
                    were no smarter than you. And you can change it, you can influence
                    it, you can build your own things that other people can use."
                    <footer class="text-sm text-slate-500 mt-2">— Steve Jobs</footer>
                  </blockquote>

                  <div>
                    <h3 class="text-white font-semibold mb-2">The Original Vision</h3>
                    <p>
                      What started as a personal goal for 2025 quickly evolved into
                      something I believe could be transformative for others too.
                      Whether you're just starting out or you're a seasoned veteran,
                      there's a place for you in this journey.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                      Together, we'll push boundaries, create freely, and grow both
                      personally and professionally. This isn't just about building
                      products — it's about building ourselves.
                    </p>
                  </div>

                  <div class="bg-slate-800/50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-700/50">
                    <h3 class="text-green-500 font-semibold mb-4 text-xl">
                      "I will become a tiny, hyperfast product lab."
                    </h3>
                    <div class="space-y-4">
                      <div>
                        <h4 class="font-semibold text-white">Ship every month to overcome fear of failure</h4>
                        <p>
                          Like many of you, I've been in tech for a while, yet I still
                          feel like a beginner sometimes. I have countless projects
                          that never saw the light of day. Shipping is better than perfect!
                        </p>
                      </div>
                      <div>
                        <h4 class="font-semibold text-white">Ship every month to increase probability of success</h4>
                        <p>
                          We often hear "idea is cheap, execution is key." Shipping
                          monthly increases our chances of success by letting the
                          market, not our doubts, decide what works.
                        </p>
                      </div>
                      <div>
                        <h4 class="font-semibold text-white">Shipping every month sounds fun!</h4>
                        <p>
                          Creating is fun! Seeing your creation used by others is even
                          better. This is our playground for freedom and creativity.
                        </p>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>

                  <div>
                    <h3 class="text-white font-semibold mb-2">Original Rules</h3>
                    <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2">
                      <li>Launch a product each month — no excuses</li>
                      <li>Product has to be paid — forces real value creation</li>
                      <li>Marketing is key — building is just the start</li>
                    </ol>
                  </div>

                  <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 italic">
                    These were the original rules. The platform has since evolved to
                    welcome builders at any pace and for any motivation — not just paid products.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </details>
            </section>

            <hr class="border-slate-700" />

            <section class="text-center">
              <h2 class="text-gradient">Ready to Bet on Yourself?</h2>
              <p class="mb-8">
                Join a community of builders who ship. Your journey starts now.
              </p>
              <a
                href="/join"
                class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full px-6 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-white bg-gradient-to-r from-primary-600 to-accent-500 hover:from-primary-700 hover:to-accent-600 transition-all"
              >
                Join & Build Today
              </a>
            </section>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </main>

    <Footer />
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .prose {
    max-width: 65ch;
  }
  .prose h2 {
    @apply text-2xl font-bold mb-4;
  }
  .prose p {
    @apply text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-4;
  }
  details summary::-webkit-details-marker {
    display: none;
  }
</style>
